http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/Kejriwal-appears-in-Mumbai-court/article14010072.ece

Delhi chief minister Arvind Kejriwal on Wednesday surrendered a bail bond of Rs. 10,000 and a surety at the Kurla magistrate court, in Mumbai.Metropolitan Magistrate Richa Khedekar who also presided over the recent drink and drive case of Janhavi Gadkar, accepted the papers and let the CM leave the court.Mr. Kejriwal and former CEO of Bank of Scotland Meera Sanyal were present in court. The Aam Aadmi Party leader and other members were booked for holding an "unscheduled" rally in Mankhurd without prior permissions from the Mumbai traffic police.The rally was held during the 2014 Lok Sabha polls and relevant sections of Mumbai Police Act were levied upon them. While Medha Patkar and Ms. Sanyal's bail bond procedures were already done, the CM had to be present today to complete his procedures.Satish Jain, a Mumbai Lok Sabha member of the Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) filed a surety in court. Mr. Kejriwal left for a function at Sofitel Hotel in Bandra Kurla Complex for a meeting and will fly out of the city in the evening.On December 9 last year, the magistrate court had granted exemption from appearance to the party superemo till today. While the CM has been asked to leave the court, the arguments seeking his permanent exemption will take place in the second half of the day.